$ PHP code snippets: variables

{ isset() #php-isset

 `isset($var)` returns `TRUE` if the variable `$var` is a declared value and its value is different from `NULL`. Otherwise, it returns `FALSE`.

  gh|about-php|/isset.html||

  Compare with → development/web/php/snippets/null-empty#php-empty[`empty()`].

  In order to check if a key exists in a → development/web/php/snippets/array/associative[associative array], the function → development/web/php/snippets/array/associative#php-array_key_exists[`array_key_exists()`] can be used.

}
{ var_dump()

 `var_dump()` shows information about one or more variables.

  gh|about-php|/variable/var_dump.html||

  This example prints
code {
int(42)
string(11) "Hello world"
array(3) {
  [0]=>
  string(3) "foo"
  [1]=>
  string(3) "bar"
  [2]=>
  string(3) "baz"
}
array(2) {
  ["num"]=>
  int(99)
  ["txt"]=>
  string(4) "ciao"
}
code }

}

